<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--NorthwestPilots 1stLd-Writethru a0691 08-21 0148</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Northwest Pilots, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0691,0147</SECOND>
<HEAD>Northwest Pilots Ratify New Contract</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS lead to CORRECT name of pilots union.</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Eastern Pilots</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAGAN, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northwest Airlines pilots have ratified a
tentative contract offer with NWA Inc. that ends 2{ years of
negotiations, the Air Line Pilots Association reported Monday.
   The Northwest Master Executive Council ratified the contract
Sunday.
   The same contract was ratified last week by co-workers who are
former Republic Airlines pilots.
   The joint ratification covers 5,200 pilots and marks the first
time both pilot groups will be working under the same contract since
the Northwest-Republic merger in 1986.
   The agreement will boost pay between 16 percent and 37 percent
over its five-year life and create a separate, lower wage scale for
new hires.
   It also calls for job security measures to protect against
possible restructurings by the carrier's new owners.
</TEXT>
