League's Most Valuable Player last year.
   He was arrested in San Francisco April 21 after a passer-by
noticed a fully loaded, semi-automatic pistol on the floor of his
parked Jaguar.
   His lawyer said Canseco plans to plead no contest in that case to
a misdemeanor weapons charge in exchange for probation and community
service.
