company worth about $250 million, says TV Guide magazine.
   Miss Winfrey, 35, has ``become so valuable to King World
(syndicator of her show) that a Wall Street analyst estimated the
company maintains a $50 to $70 million insurance policy on her
life,'' the magazine said in its Aug. 26 edition.
   The next seven richest were Marcy Carsey, Mary Tyler Moore, Agnes
Nixon, Esther Shapiro, Susan Harris, Carol Burnett and Joan Rivers.
The wealth ratings were based on public documents, reports and
interviews, TV Guide said.
   All eight women are producers, owners or creators of shows with
the exception of Ms. Rivers, whose $30 million worth was said to
come from real estate.
   Miss Winfrey stars in, owns and produces ``The Oprah Winfrey
Show,'' is co-owner of a Chicago television and movie studio, part
owner of three television stations, a partner in a Chicago
restaurant and owns a 160-acre farm in Indiana.
