<FIRST>r w AM-CatfishOutput     08-21 0106</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Catfish Output,100</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Up, Prices Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Catfish farmers continue to boost production,
but their harvests are bringing lower prices than a year ago, the
Agriculture Department said Monday.
   Production in July totaled 27.8 million pounds of live weight
delivered to processing plants, the department said in its monthly
report. That was up 17 percent from July 1988.
   But prices paid to growers averaged 71 cents per pound, down nine
cents a pound from a year earlier, the report said.
   Production through the first seven months of 1989 totaled 196.6
million pounds, up 16 percent from the same period of last year.
