its recent ban on ostrich imports to include related flightless
birds such as emus, rheas and cassowaries because they may carry
disease-bearing parasites.
   Larry B. Slagle, acting administrator of the department's Animal
and Plant Health Inspection Service, said Friday the expanded import
ban was effective immediately and would remain indefinitely.
</TEXT>
