Newgateway PLC for majority control of British supermarket operator
Gateway Corp. PLC, has reached a truce with its rival, which still
owns 40 percent of Gateway.
   Newgateway, which comprises U.S. financiers Wasserstein Perella
and Co. and the Great Atlantic and Pacific Tea Co., agreed Friday to
exchange its holding for a proportionate stake in Isosceles. It will
be represented on Gateway's board and will support Isosceles in
implementing ``its commercial strategy.''
</TEXT>
