<TEXT>
   The stock market closed higher Friday, as the Dow Jones average
of 30 industrials rose 8.34 points to 2,687.97, a gain of 3.98
points on the week.
   The dollar slipped in worldwide trading.
   Bond prices finished narrowly mixed.
   Copper and precious metals futures retreated while futures prices
for energy, grains, soybeans, livestock and meat were mixed.
