rates, included: 1.9627 West German marks, up from 1.9555; 1.6920
Swiss francs, up from 1.6860; 6.6155 French francs, up from 6.5945;
2.2150 Dutch guilders, up from 2.2080; 1,408.00 Italian lire, up
from 1,405.75; and 1.1770 Canadian dollars, down from 1.1787.
   Earlier in Tokyo, where markets close before Europe's business
day begins, the dollar closed at 143.35 Japanese yen, down 0.17 yen.
In London, the dollar traded at 142.80 yen.
   Gold opened in London, the major market, at $365.15 a troy ounce,
down from $366.65 late Friday. At midmorning, the city's bullion
dealers fixed a recommended price of $365.50.
   The Zurich price was $365.30, down from $366.75.
   Earlier in Hong Kong, gold closed at $366.79 bid, down 22 cents.
   Silver bullion traded in London at $5.22 a troy ounce, down from
$5.25.
