<FIRST>a f AM-BusinessMirror CORRECTIVE   08-21 0070</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Business Mirror, CORRECTIVE,0071</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds:Members who used f0116, AM-Business Mirror advance for Aug. 3,
are asked to use the following.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press erroneously reported Aug. 2
that 4 percent inflation reduces the value of a dollar to 50 cents
in 13 years.
   Using the principle known as the Rule of 72, 4 percent inflation
actually cuts a dollar to 50 cents in 18 years.
</TEXT>
