<FIRST>u f BC-BritishStocks 1stLd-Writethru   08-21 0195</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-British Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0201</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares End Slightly Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with later activity, closing index;
No pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices fell slightly Monday on the London
Stock Exchange, as conflicting factors affecting the market canceled
each other out.
   The market was buoyed by selective buying interest on a range of
stocks, traders said.
   However, an early round of selling, combined with a weak opening
on Wall Street, served to upset the market's upward move.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed 0.4
points, or 0.02 percent, lower at 2,374.7, down from a session high
of 2,383.8. The market posted a session low of 2,368.1.
   Volume totaled 349.7 million shares, down from 378.4 million
traded on Friday.
   ``There is a stalemate between buyers and sellers at the
moment,'' one trader said. ``The market's looking for fresh
inspiration to move decisively one way or the other.''
   The Financial Times 30-share index ended down 10 points at
1,969.0. The Financial Times 500-share index slipped 0.83 point to
close at 1,333.57.
   At the London close, the Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was
down 15.17 points at 2,672.80 in New York.
</TEXT>
