<HEAD>Pratt &amp; Whitney Receives Order Worth $162 Million from Northwest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAST HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northwest Airlines has ordered 12
Pratt &amp; Whitney PW4000 series engines to power six Airbus Industrie
A330 twinjets, an order worth about $162 million, Pratt &amp; Whitney
said Monday.
   Last February, Northwest became the first U.S. carrier to
purchase A330s when it ordered 10 of the planes, also powered by
PW4000 engines. The latest order for six additional aircraft brings
to 16 the total number of A330s that Northwest has on firm order.
   Northwest is also equipping its fleet of 10 Boeing 747-400
aircraft with PW4000 engines.
   Pratt &amp; Whitney is a unit of Hartford-based United Technologies
Corp. UTC sells a variety of high-technology products and support
services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive
industries.
</TEXT>
