<FIRST>u f AM-Japan-Markets     08-21 0176</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Japan-Markets,0184</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dollar, Stock Prices Ease in Early Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar eased in early trading against the
Japanese yen Tuesday, while stock prices on the Tokyo Stock Exchange
fell moderately.
   The dollar started trading at 142.78 yen, down 0.57 yen from
Monday's close of 143.35 yen. It closed at 143.08 yen in New York
overnight.
   ``It's moving narrowly as many market players are taking a
wait-and-see position'' in anticipation of the U.S. Federal Reserve
Board's open market committee meeting, to be held in Washigton later
Tuesday, said a dealer with the Bank of Tokyo, who spoke anonymously.
   The Fed committee is expected to discuss interest rates and other
economic matters.
   On the stock market, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected
issues, which gained 77.69 points for a record closing of 35,140.83
Monday, shed 121.19 points, or 0.34 percent, shortly after the
market opened to move to 35,019.64.
   The drop in the Nikkei reflected a 40.97-point decline in the Dow
Jones Stock Average on Monday in New York, dealers said.
</TEXT>
